    "Name": "Big Foot",
    "Details": "A rarely seen alternative to the standard BattleMaster that was released by Field Arms Systems Associates based on the plans for the standard BattleMaster they obtained through industrial espionage. Only a few variants of this mech were produced before legal troubles forced the manufacturing to stop. Nevertheless it is just as effective a design as the standard BattleMaster and shares many compatible spare parts, making it feasible to maintain for the forces that wound up purchasing it. The 3M variant was apparently the most expensive variant sold by Field Arms Systems, using an ER PPC and double heatsinks, the price meant that very few examples of this were built before the legal troubles ended manufacturing of the mech for good.<br><br>S-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that substantially improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
